1
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:10,666
You don't need to fight
in the team tournament.

2
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:13,708
[groans]

3
00:00:13,791 --> 00:00:15,333
[OZEKI]
Just as I thought.

4
00:00:15,416 --> 00:00:17,083
Were you planning
on telling us?

5
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:20,875
[HINOMARU] I'm perfectly fine!
This is nothing!

6
00:00:20,958 --> 00:00:23,833
[OZEKI] Tsuji's calling
for a taxi to come pick you up.

7
00:00:23,916 --> 00:00:25,625
Then you're going
to the hospital.

8
00:00:26,708 --> 00:00:28,333
You're not done, Ushio.

9
00:00:29,333 --> 00:00:31,791
Your dream of joining
the pro league isn't over.

10
00:00:31,875 --> 00:00:34,375
Not as long as the team
tournament's still up for grabs.

11
00:02:11,083 --> 00:02:13,750
♪

12
00:02:17,375 --> 00:02:18,875
[knocking on door]

13
00:02:18,958 --> 00:02:21,666
It's Shibakiyama!
Open up, Doc!

14
00:02:21,750 --> 00:02:23,750
[knocking on door continues]

15
00:02:23,833 --> 00:02:25,791
[DOCTOR]
I heard ya, I heard ya.

16
00:02:25,875 --> 00:02:27,208
[door opens]

17
00:02:27,291 --> 00:02:29,791
Keep it down, will ya,
Kaorucchi?

18
00:02:29,875 --> 00:02:32,333
You wouldn't believe
the savage hangover I've got.

19
00:02:33,541 --> 00:02:36,416
[HINOMARU]
Um, I'm not so sure about this.

20
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:39,333
[CROWD cheering]

21
00:02:39,416 --> 00:02:41,500
♪

22
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:48,666
[KANAMORI]
That's impossible.

23
00:02:48,750 --> 00:02:50,666
He pushed me out of the ring?

24
00:02:50,750 --> 00:02:52,708
♪

25
00:02:52,791 --> 00:02:55,458
It's not like he gave up
on using strikes.

26
00:02:55,541 --> 00:02:58,708
Tenma's just been practicing,
and now he's a grappling master.

27
00:02:58,791 --> 00:03:01,958
[CROWD applauding]

28
00:03:02,041 --> 00:03:04,708
[ANNOUNCER] That concludes
today's individual bouts.

29
00:03:06,458 --> 00:03:08,958
Team tournament
preliminary bouts

30
00:03:09,041 --> 00:03:10,458
will begin now.

31
00:03:10,541 --> 00:03:12,958
♪

32
00:03:15,166 --> 00:03:18,666
[DOCTOR]
Uh, Hinomaru... Ushio.

33
00:03:18,750 --> 00:03:20,750
Fifteen years of age.

34
00:03:21,875 --> 00:03:23,583
[HINOMARU]
This dump's worse than my place.

35
00:03:23,666 --> 00:03:27,541
Uh! 152 centimeters tall?
He's tiny!

36
00:03:27,625 --> 00:03:30,416
Big deal.
I'm still gonna be a pro!

37
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:32,291
Come on, kid!

38
00:03:32,375 --> 00:03:33,958
You know there's
a physical, right?

39
00:03:34,041 --> 00:03:37,083
Get your head out of the clouds
and join reality.

40
00:03:37,166 --> 00:03:39,958
I'm a busy man,
and look how sunny it is.

41
00:03:40,041 --> 00:03:42,416
Shine on, Mr. Sun.
Shine on.

42
00:03:42,500 --> 00:03:44,916
Blue seas,
white sandy beaches.

43
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,333
Tanned, taut bodies
in colorful bikinis.

44
00:03:47,416 --> 00:03:49,250
Summer. And it's calling
my name.

45
00:03:49,333 --> 00:03:50,916
Ignoring it would be criminal.

46
00:03:52,916 --> 00:03:55,250
Hey, first impressions
aren't everything.

47
00:03:56,791 --> 00:03:58,625
[DOCTOR]
Gotta go. Ciao.

48
00:03:58,708 --> 00:04:00,000
Excuse me!

49
00:04:00,083 --> 00:04:01,000
[DOCTOR]
Now what?

50
00:04:01,083 --> 00:04:02,625
You don't get it!

51
00:04:02,708 --> 00:04:05,500
My teammates are waiting
for me to get back!

52
00:04:05,583 --> 00:04:08,541
♪

53
00:04:11,583 --> 00:04:14,166
We must be a magnet
for bad luck.

54
00:04:14,250 --> 00:04:16,416
I mean, drawing last year's
third-place team

55
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:18,000
in the first round?
Come on!

56
00:04:18,083 --> 00:04:19,625
And three of the competitors

57
00:04:19,708 --> 00:04:22,041
we'll be facing participated
in that tournament.

58
00:04:22,125 --> 00:04:23,125
Huh?

59
00:04:23,208 --> 00:04:24,833
[CHIZUKO]
That's not all.

60
00:04:24,916 --> 00:04:27,916
Among the competitors is
national treasure Hikage Tenma.

61
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,666
♪

62
00:04:29,750 --> 00:04:31,583
So what you're saying is,

63
00:04:31,666 --> 00:04:33,458
we could be
seriously screwed here.

64
00:04:34,541 --> 00:04:36,791
[ANNOUNCER] For the next match,
on the east side,

65
00:04:36,875 --> 00:04:38,250
Odachi High School.

66
00:04:38,333 --> 00:04:40,375
On the west side,
Kanazawa Kita High School.

67
00:04:40,458 --> 00:04:41,916
[YUMA]
Okay, go get 'em!

68
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:44,625
[ANNOUNCER] First bout.
On the east side, Ozeki.

69
00:04:44,708 --> 00:04:45,708
Yeah!

70
00:04:47,166 --> 00:04:49,583
On the west side, Aizawa.

71
00:04:49,666 --> 00:04:53,000
-Bring the pain, Captain!
-You got this!

72
00:04:53,083 --> 00:04:54,791
That's Ryo Aizawa.

73
00:04:54,875 --> 00:04:56,375
“Swift Foot Pull.”

74
00:04:56,458 --> 00:04:57,833
Although not the biggest,

75
00:04:57,916 --> 00:04:59,166
he's the captain
of the formidable

76
00:04:59,250 --> 00:05:00,500
Kita High team.

77
00:05:00,583 --> 00:05:01,708
He's deadly.

78
00:05:01,791 --> 00:05:05,041
♪

79
00:05:06,041 --> 00:05:07,500
[DOCTOR]
I'm not gettin' any younger.

80
00:05:07,583 --> 00:05:09,000
I don't see the point
in wasting my time.

81
00:05:09,083 --> 00:05:10,416
"Wasting"?

82
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:11,541
Your team's up against

83
00:05:11,625 --> 00:05:13,750
Kanazawa Kita High
first round.

84
00:05:13,833 --> 00:05:15,916
Just between us,
you don't actually expect them

85
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,500
to win, do you?

86
00:05:19,041 --> 00:05:20,625
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
Hmm?

87
00:05:20,708 --> 00:05:23,000
♪

88
00:05:23,083 --> 00:05:24,833
[DOCTOR]
The kid went into standby.

89
00:05:24,916 --> 00:05:26,916
Did you understand the question?

90
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,791
[HINOMARU]
Now that I think about it,

91
00:05:28,875 --> 00:05:30,791
I guess there's a chance
they could lose.

92
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:33,458
What?

93
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:36,375
But the thought never crossed
my mind until just now.

94
00:05:36,458 --> 00:05:37,416
Uh...

95
00:05:38,458 --> 00:05:39,250
[REFEREE]
Spirit!

96
00:05:39,333 --> 00:05:41,791
[grunts]

97
00:05:43,208 --> 00:05:44,166
[panting]

98
00:05:44,250 --> 00:05:45,625
[ALL gasp]

99
00:05:45,708 --> 00:05:47,125
[BOTH gasp]

100
00:05:47,208 --> 00:05:48,708
[gasps]

101
00:05:48,791 --> 00:05:51,041
[yelling]

102
00:05:51,125 --> 00:05:53,541
[ALL yelling]

103
00:05:53,625 --> 00:05:55,083
You know,

104
00:05:55,166 --> 00:05:56,958
hearing I wasn't needed
at the team tournament

105
00:05:57,041 --> 00:05:58,083
was a shock.

106
00:05:58,166 --> 00:05:59,250
It made me nervous.

107
00:06:00,250 --> 00:06:01,625
But after I listened
to the captain

108
00:06:01,708 --> 00:06:03,125
and saw the look
the rest of the team

109
00:06:03,208 --> 00:06:04,625
had in their eyes...

110
00:06:04,708 --> 00:06:07,458
I suddenly felt relaxed
about the whole thing.

111
00:06:09,041 --> 00:06:10,791
This isn't about them
needing my help

112
00:06:10,875 --> 00:06:12,958
or how they can't win
without me.

113
00:06:13,041 --> 00:06:15,000
I just need
to fight with them.

114
00:06:15,083 --> 00:06:17,583
Right now,
that's all I want.

115
00:06:20,083 --> 00:06:21,250
[sighs]

116
00:06:22,250 --> 00:06:24,208
Well, let's see it.

117
00:06:28,916 --> 00:06:30,166
[HINOMARU grunts]

118
00:06:31,541 --> 00:06:33,708
If you care
about your career,

119
00:06:33,791 --> 00:06:35,208
it'd be better for you
in the long run

120
00:06:35,291 --> 00:06:36,625
to sit this one out.

121
00:06:38,625 --> 00:06:39,875
Yep!

122
00:06:39,958 --> 00:06:41,208
That's what a doctor
with any common sense

123
00:06:41,291 --> 00:06:42,500
would tell ya!

124
00:06:42,583 --> 00:06:43,625
Hmm?

125
00:06:44,625 --> 00:06:45,958
I swear.

126
00:06:46,041 --> 00:06:48,083
I wish I knew
where you got your moxie from.

127
00:06:48,166 --> 00:06:50,083
How about sharing it
with the rest of us?

128
00:06:51,458 --> 00:06:55,041
Listen, kid, I've treated a lot
of sumo wrestlers in my time.

129
00:06:55,125 --> 00:06:56,416
Some of them were
too messed up

130
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:58,833
to even step foot
back inside the ring.

131
00:06:58,916 --> 00:07:01,458
But that didn't stop them
from coming to see me.

132
00:07:02,791 --> 00:07:04,750
Getting your arm back in shape
will be easier

133
00:07:04,833 --> 00:07:06,000
than cutting a fart.

134
00:07:08,041 --> 00:07:09,958
[HINOMARU] What is this?
A spaceship?

135
00:07:10,958 --> 00:07:12,583
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
I never get over this room.

136
00:07:12,666 --> 00:07:14,375
By the way, when are you
gonna bite the bullet

137
00:07:14,458 --> 00:07:16,250
and invest in a new sign, Doc?

138
00:07:16,333 --> 00:07:19,500
I like the sign.
It's got a certain charm.

139
00:07:22,708 --> 00:07:23,916
This way.

140
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,833
Let's get that arm
working again.

141
00:07:26,875 --> 00:07:28,208
That's surprising.

142
00:07:28,291 --> 00:07:30,125
Ozeki's the last person
I could imagine

143
00:07:30,208 --> 00:07:32,041
going full-on beast mode.

144
00:07:32,125 --> 00:07:34,250
I guess
that settles it, then.

145
00:07:34,333 --> 00:07:36,583
Beating you at the prelims
wasn't just a fluke.

146
00:07:37,583 --> 00:07:40,041
And he's only gotten stronger
since then.

147
00:07:40,125 --> 00:07:41,958
Here I was thinking
Onimaru's absence

148
00:07:42,041 --> 00:07:43,541
would be weighing on him.

149
00:07:43,625 --> 00:07:46,208
But apparently it only made him
more determined to win.

150
00:07:47,208 --> 00:07:50,041
His expression and technique
were full of spirit.

151
00:07:50,125 --> 00:07:53,791
There's a face that shouts
"I'm Dachi High's captain!"

152
00:07:53,875 --> 00:07:56,041
By the way,
look who's up next.

153
00:07:56,125 --> 00:07:58,291
-Your favorite fighter.
-Huh?

154
00:07:59,583 --> 00:08:03,083
[ANNOUNCER] Second bout.
On the east side, Gojo.

155
00:08:05,708 --> 00:08:07,416
-Go, Yuma!
-Hail the king!

156
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:09,416
[HINOMARU]
Before he joined the sumo club,

157
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:10,583
he used to be a delinquent.

158
00:08:10,666 --> 00:08:11,666
Huh?

159
00:08:11,750 --> 00:08:12,750
But...

160
00:08:13,791 --> 00:08:15,750
he's different now.
Trust me.

161
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:18,125
[REFEREE]
Spirit!

162
00:08:18,208 --> 00:08:19,250
[growling]

163
00:08:19,333 --> 00:08:20,291
[YUMA]
Uh...

164
00:08:22,375 --> 00:08:24,291
He was ready
for the two-handed strike!

165
00:08:24,375 --> 00:08:27,291
That's Takumi Sera!
His strength is incredible!

166
00:08:27,375 --> 00:08:29,375
He placed fourth
in the Ishikawa tournament.

167
00:08:29,458 --> 00:08:31,041
[SERA]
Think I'm intimidated?

168
00:08:31,125 --> 00:08:32,958
I withstand
Tenma's strikes every day!

169
00:08:33,041 --> 00:08:34,791
[growling]

170
00:08:34,875 --> 00:08:35,875
Bring it!

171
00:08:37,541 --> 00:08:38,791
[HINOMARU]
Honestly,

172
00:08:38,875 --> 00:08:41,041
when I first met him
during his kingpin days,

173
00:08:41,125 --> 00:08:43,708
I thought the guy belonged
in an entirely different decade.

174
00:08:44,875 --> 00:08:46,500
But after we fought
and he admitted defeat

175
00:08:46,583 --> 00:08:48,208
by bowing his head,

176
00:08:48,291 --> 00:08:50,125
I knew that he was okay.

177
00:08:50,208 --> 00:08:53,208
Before you can improve,
you need humility.

178
00:08:53,291 --> 00:08:55,833
Without it, the thought
of combining sumo and karate

179
00:08:55,916 --> 00:08:57,041
would be completely crazy,

180
00:08:57,125 --> 00:08:58,833
but he found a way
to marry the two.

181
00:08:59,833 --> 00:09:01,833
We're expecting
great things out of him.

182
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:07,250
[groaning]

183
00:09:07,333 --> 00:09:09,500
[SERA]
He's too fast!

184
00:09:10,666 --> 00:09:12,125
[KANAMORI]
Rather than pushing back,

185
00:09:12,208 --> 00:09:14,000
his opponent's ricocheting.

186
00:09:14,083 --> 00:09:16,625
Each blow's hitting him in a
completely different direction.

187
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,458
Sera couldn't make a grab

188
00:09:19,541 --> 00:09:22,708
against that karate-like
snapping even if he wanted to.

189
00:09:22,791 --> 00:09:24,250
That was your mistake.

190
00:09:24,333 --> 00:09:26,541
You shouldn't have
let him build momentum.

191
00:09:26,625 --> 00:09:28,375
Wearing me down, huh?

192
00:09:28,458 --> 00:09:31,083
Yeah, right.
I'm ending you right now!

193
00:09:31,166 --> 00:09:32,916
♪

194
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:36,416
[YUMA] Trip and strike.
Castle Break Punch!

195
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:39,208
♪

196
00:09:39,291 --> 00:09:41,250
[SERA grunts]

197
00:09:41,333 --> 00:09:43,541
Yeah!

198
00:09:43,625 --> 00:09:46,541
[CROWD cheering]

199
00:09:46,625 --> 00:09:47,916
Yes!

200
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,333
-Yuma!
-[CHIZUKO giggles]

201
00:09:49,416 --> 00:09:50,708
[HASHI/NISHIZATO]
Get 'em, boss!

202
00:09:50,791 --> 00:09:52,333
That was awesome, Yuma!

203
00:09:52,416 --> 00:09:54,833
[MAN 1] Looks like
Kita High's washed up.

204
00:09:54,916 --> 00:09:56,875
[MAN 2] A powerhouse team?
Yeah, right!

205
00:10:00,291 --> 00:10:02,750
Both teams wanted
to carve out an early lead.

206
00:10:02,833 --> 00:10:05,000
Two wins in a row
is a huge deal!

207
00:10:05,083 --> 00:10:07,666
They're in a solid spot
right now.

208
00:10:07,750 --> 00:10:10,583
Yes, but this next bout
will be a problem.

209
00:10:10,666 --> 00:10:13,625
Their third opponent's going
to be a much bigger challenge.

210
00:10:13,708 --> 00:10:15,625
Literally.

211
00:10:15,708 --> 00:10:18,166
[AIZAWA]
It's all up to you, Tenma.

212
00:10:18,250 --> 00:10:19,500
[TENMA]
Hmm?

213
00:10:19,583 --> 00:10:20,958
You don't need encouragement

214
00:10:21,041 --> 00:10:22,875
from your sorry excuse
for a captain,

215
00:10:22,958 --> 00:10:25,458
and I know a national treasure
can handle himself,

216
00:10:25,541 --> 00:10:27,458
especially against an amateur.

217
00:10:27,541 --> 00:10:29,833
But I want to say this
to you anyway.

218
00:10:30,958 --> 00:10:32,666
Go out there and win!

219
00:10:34,333 --> 00:10:36,708
Damn it!
I'm sorry, guys!

220
00:10:36,791 --> 00:10:38,375
[groans]

221
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,833
What a bunch
of pathetic teammates.

222
00:10:42,916 --> 00:10:44,291
Huh?

223
00:10:44,375 --> 00:10:45,708
[TENMA] A national treasure
who fails to become

224
00:10:45,791 --> 00:10:47,583
a high school yokozuna.

225
00:10:47,666 --> 00:10:50,708
A renowned school
without a championship.

226
00:10:50,791 --> 00:10:53,541
I don't know about you,
but I'm here to change all that.

227
00:10:53,625 --> 00:10:54,708
Watch and learn.

228
00:10:56,916 --> 00:11:00,125
Yone. Komori.
Prepare for your bouts.

229
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:09,208
You better be paying attention.

230
00:11:09,291 --> 00:11:11,208
Ishigami won't win
the finals next year

231
00:11:11,291 --> 00:11:13,750
if you don't come up with a plan
for how to defeat this guy.

232
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:15,208
Hey, Captain,

233
00:11:15,291 --> 00:11:16,875
which one are you
talkin' about?

234
00:11:18,291 --> 00:11:19,458
[ANNOUNCER]
Third bout.

235
00:11:19,541 --> 00:11:22,250
On the east side, Kunisaki.

236
00:11:24,500 --> 00:11:27,083
[DOCTOR] So your teammate's
a renowned wrestling champion?

237
00:11:27,166 --> 00:11:28,625
Impressive.

238
00:11:28,708 --> 00:11:31,083
But he's only been doing sumo
for a few months, right?

239
00:11:31,166 --> 00:11:32,666
And he's fighting
someone like that?

240
00:11:33,708 --> 00:11:35,333
[HINOMARU] I don't like
throwing the word around,

241
00:11:35,416 --> 00:11:38,333
but, in his case,
I'll gladly make an exception,

242
00:11:38,416 --> 00:11:40,333
'cause there's no other way
to describe him.

243
00:11:40,416 --> 00:11:42,166
♪

244
00:11:42,250 --> 00:11:43,250
The truth is...

245
00:11:43,333 --> 00:11:46,625
♪

246
00:11:46,708 --> 00:11:48,375
[HINOMARU/SADA]
Chihiro Kunisaki...

247
00:11:49,875 --> 00:11:51,875
is a genius.

248
00:11:51,958 --> 00:11:54,291
♪

249
00:11:57,541 --> 00:12:02,000
♪

250
00:12:02,083 --> 00:12:05,000
[CHIHIRO] He's got a 20
centimeter advantage over me.

251
00:12:05,083 --> 00:12:08,000
This must be what Hinomaru
feels like all the time.

252
00:12:08,083 --> 00:12:11,375
♪

253
00:12:11,458 --> 00:12:12,500
[CHIHIRO chuckles]

254
00:12:12,583 --> 00:12:14,541
♪

255
00:12:14,625 --> 00:12:16,458
[CROWD murmuring]

256
00:12:16,541 --> 00:12:18,041
Hmm?

257
00:12:18,125 --> 00:12:20,750
[CHIHIRO] All right,
Mr. National Treasure.

258
00:12:20,833 --> 00:12:22,000
How you gonna attack?

259
00:12:25,208 --> 00:12:26,750
At that distance,
he's a sitting duck

260
00:12:26,833 --> 00:12:29,416
for one of the best strikers
in high school sumo.

261
00:12:29,500 --> 00:12:32,541
Maybe he's planning on charging
and going in low.

262
00:12:32,625 --> 00:12:34,958
[KANAMORI] Show me
what you're made of, Kunisaki.

263
00:12:35,041 --> 00:12:38,333
Even Sada acknowledges
your talent.

264
00:12:38,416 --> 00:12:41,708
I want to see what you can do
against an elite fighter.

265
00:12:41,791 --> 00:12:43,541
[REFEREE]
Spirit!

266
00:12:43,625 --> 00:12:45,333
[grunting]

267
00:12:45,416 --> 00:12:47,375
[groaning]

268
00:12:47,458 --> 00:12:48,833
[gasping]

269
00:12:48,916 --> 00:12:51,291
Even charging full speed,
he wasn't quick enough!

270
00:12:51,375 --> 00:12:52,916
Did you really think
you'd be safe

271
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:54,666
if you held back like that?

272
00:12:54,750 --> 00:12:57,583
Nearly the entire sumo ring
is within his range.

273
00:12:57,666 --> 00:13:01,375
His speed, power,
they're completely unmatched!

274
00:13:01,458 --> 00:13:04,083
There's no better example
than his Flash Attack!

275
00:13:05,375 --> 00:13:07,416
[CHIHIRO grunting]

276
00:13:09,875 --> 00:13:11,291
Oh!

277
00:13:11,375 --> 00:13:13,041
Kunisaki's getting destroyed!

278
00:13:13,125 --> 00:13:15,291
He can't get in a single hit!

279
00:13:15,375 --> 00:13:17,166
I guess he was nowhere
near ready

280
00:13:17,250 --> 00:13:18,958
to take on
a national treasure.

281
00:13:20,041 --> 00:13:21,625
[CHIHIRO] If I want
to become a better fighter,

282
00:13:21,708 --> 00:13:23,791
my sumo needs a ton of work.

283
00:13:25,833 --> 00:13:27,625
I realize I don't have
enough time

284
00:13:27,708 --> 00:13:29,333
to get there on my own.

285
00:13:29,416 --> 00:13:30,666
So here's the plan.

286
00:13:30,750 --> 00:13:33,083
I'm gonna absorb
your sumo style

287
00:13:33,166 --> 00:13:35,000
and then soar
straight to the top!

288
00:13:42,333 --> 00:13:43,333
Uh...

289
00:13:43,416 --> 00:13:44,666
[gasps]

290
00:13:44,750 --> 00:13:46,125
Yes!

291
00:13:46,208 --> 00:13:47,833
Was he holding back
all this time

292
00:13:47,916 --> 00:13:50,083
so he could evaluate
Hikage's attack pattern?

293
00:13:50,166 --> 00:13:52,500
He sure had to take
a pummeling to do it, though.

294
00:13:52,583 --> 00:13:54,333
The best strikes
in high school sumo

295
00:13:54,416 --> 00:13:57,125
turned out to be more brutal
than he was expecting.

296
00:13:57,208 --> 00:13:59,125
Of course he had a rough time
seeing through them.

297
00:13:59,208 --> 00:14:00,958
Wait just a minute.

298
00:14:01,041 --> 00:14:03,000
Are you telling me
between the prelims and now,

299
00:14:03,083 --> 00:14:05,041
he completely adopted
your style?

300
00:14:05,125 --> 00:14:07,333
The longer you spend wrestling
with the guy,

301
00:14:07,416 --> 00:14:09,375
the more he starts
to creep you out.

302
00:14:10,458 --> 00:14:14,541
[CHIHIRO] I want more.
Show me more!

303
00:14:14,625 --> 00:14:16,916
[SADA] He may lack experience
in the sumo ring,

304
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:19,750
but he makes up for it
with his powers of observation.

305
00:14:19,833 --> 00:14:21,083
That's the secret
of how he's able

306
00:14:21,166 --> 00:14:23,291
to absorb techniques
so quickly.

307
00:14:24,458 --> 00:14:25,916
It kinda pisses me off.

308
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:28,708
Here I am, not making it
past the prelims.

309
00:14:28,791 --> 00:14:29,916
But there are my moves.

310
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,750
It's like I'm fighting.

311
00:14:33,333 --> 00:14:34,875
[TENMA]
Mikazuki Munechika?

312
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:37,708
[CHIHIRO]
So that was the heaviest blow

313
00:14:37,791 --> 00:14:39,208
in all of high school sumo?

314
00:14:40,208 --> 00:14:44,250
Well, if that's the case,
there's nothing left to fear!

315
00:14:44,333 --> 00:14:46,625
He outmaneuvered
Odenta's strike!

316
00:14:46,708 --> 00:14:49,000
♪

317
00:14:49,083 --> 00:14:50,000
Huh?

318
00:14:50,083 --> 00:14:51,375
♪

319
00:14:53,375 --> 00:14:55,083
An over-the-shoulder grab!

320
00:14:55,166 --> 00:14:56,583
His reach is incredible!

321
00:14:56,666 --> 00:14:58,958
But Kunisaki has
a stronger stance!

322
00:14:59,041 --> 00:15:00,166
He can do it!

323
00:15:01,375 --> 00:15:03,750
[TENMA] I can hear them
all laughing at me.

324
00:15:03,833 --> 00:15:07,041
The expectations are high
since I'm a national treasure.

325
00:15:07,125 --> 00:15:09,583
But here I am, losing to a guy
who was a plain wrestler

326
00:15:09,666 --> 00:15:11,000
till a few months ago.

327
00:15:12,791 --> 00:15:14,666
I've already told you,
I've got zero interest

328
00:15:14,750 --> 00:15:16,541
in watching my brother compete.

329
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:20,000
He'll win,
but only by just enough.

330
00:15:21,333 --> 00:15:23,500
And of course there's no way
he'll beat a yokozuna.

331
00:15:23,583 --> 00:15:24,833
Hey!

332
00:15:24,916 --> 00:15:26,416
We all know
the only thing he's focused on

333
00:15:26,500 --> 00:15:28,291
is remaining an ozeki.

334
00:15:28,375 --> 00:15:30,250
It's truly pathetic.

335
00:15:30,333 --> 00:15:32,125
If he doesn't care about
moving up the chain,

336
00:15:32,208 --> 00:15:33,416
he should just quit.

337
00:15:36,458 --> 00:15:38,000
Damn. What was that for?

338
00:15:38,083 --> 00:15:40,750
[MAN 3] You've got no idea
what you're talking about, kid.

339
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,791
I hear that BS all the time.

340
00:15:43,875 --> 00:15:46,458
But I didn't think his own
brother would go repeating it.

341
00:15:46,541 --> 00:15:47,416
[TENMA]
Huh?

342
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:49,041
[MAN 4]
I guarantee you,

343
00:15:49,125 --> 00:15:51,500
he's got no chance
of winning this bout!

344
00:15:51,583 --> 00:15:53,375
-[TENMA] Hmm?
-[MAN 4] Seriously.

345
00:15:53,458 --> 00:15:55,916
I've totally given up
rooting for Daikeisho.

346
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:58,708
"Strongest Japanese
Sumo Wrestler" my ass.

347
00:15:58,791 --> 00:16:01,041
Yeah. Bottom line,
he just isn't hungry enough,

348
00:16:01,125 --> 00:16:02,208
so he's plateaued.

349
00:16:02,291 --> 00:16:03,583
[TENMA]
What do they know?

350
00:16:04,625 --> 00:16:06,750
If you really think
the ozeki view the arena

351
00:16:06,833 --> 00:16:08,625
as some kind of
comfortable safe haven,

352
00:16:08,708 --> 00:16:09,833
you better guess again.

353
00:16:09,916 --> 00:16:11,833
Even more reason, then.

354
00:16:11,916 --> 00:16:13,833
It'd be easier on him
if he quit!

355
00:16:13,916 --> 00:16:15,791
[MAN 3]
I thought it was obvious.

356
00:16:16,958 --> 00:16:18,083
Uh...

357
00:16:19,250 --> 00:16:22,125
♪

358
00:16:22,208 --> 00:16:23,875
[MAN 3]
He isn't broken yet.

359
00:16:23,958 --> 00:16:25,291
Far from it.

360
00:16:25,375 --> 00:16:27,208
♪

361
00:16:30,208 --> 00:16:31,416
Have you ever wondered

362
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:33,708
why you've always thought
of him as weak?

363
00:16:35,208 --> 00:16:38,208
Maybe you're projecting
your insecurities onto him.

364
00:16:38,291 --> 00:16:39,708
Uh...

365
00:16:39,791 --> 00:16:41,750
[MAN 3] You've been avoiding
looking at the ozeki

366
00:16:41,833 --> 00:16:44,291
because you see
yourself in him.

367
00:16:44,375 --> 00:16:46,375
You believe
he can't defeat a yokozuna

368
00:16:46,458 --> 00:16:48,875
only because you were unable
to beat Tennoji.

369
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,958
Maybe if you took the time,
you could learn

370
00:16:52,041 --> 00:16:53,916
a thing or two
from watching him.

371
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:56,541
Your brother's far stronger
than you think.

372
00:16:56,625 --> 00:16:58,833
[CROWD cheering]

373
00:16:58,916 --> 00:17:01,041
[TENMA]
If anyone's pathetic, it's me.

374
00:17:02,083 --> 00:17:04,708
Onimaru had that
same look in his eye.

375
00:17:04,791 --> 00:17:06,625
The look of someone
confronting a reality

376
00:17:06,708 --> 00:17:08,041
that threatens to break them.

377
00:17:08,125 --> 00:17:10,125
♪

378
00:17:10,208 --> 00:17:12,791
All I did was get annoyed
and take it out on others.

379
00:17:13,791 --> 00:17:15,291
The only loser here is me.

380
00:17:16,666 --> 00:17:18,791
I want to be
a strong sumo wrestler,

381
00:17:18,875 --> 00:17:20,166
just like my brother!

382
00:17:20,250 --> 00:17:21,958
[TENMA straining]

383
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:24,500
[KIRIHITO]
An overarm throw!

384
00:17:24,583 --> 00:17:25,916
And from that stance, too!

385
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:27,208
His reach is insane!

386
00:17:28,500 --> 00:17:30,125
[CHIHIRO straining]

387
00:17:31,250 --> 00:17:32,458
[straining]

388
00:17:35,291 --> 00:17:37,416
-He's close!
-Come on!

389
00:17:42,958 --> 00:17:46,000
[CHIHIRO] Dude's coming at me
stronger than before.

390
00:17:46,083 --> 00:17:48,958
Guess that's why they call him
a national treasure!

391
00:17:50,208 --> 00:17:53,625
I'm gonna eat you alive
and push past my limits!

392
00:18:01,458 --> 00:18:02,708
A feint?

393
00:18:03,750 --> 00:18:05,666
[TENMA]
High-Angle Head Chop!

394
00:18:05,750 --> 00:18:07,333
Lightning!

395
00:18:07,416 --> 00:18:08,791
[groaning]

396
00:18:08,875 --> 00:18:10,250
[ALL gasp]

397
00:18:10,333 --> 00:18:13,833
[SHUNKAI] So this is
Dachi High's Kunisaki.

398
00:18:13,916 --> 00:18:15,166
I see.

399
00:18:15,250 --> 00:18:17,500
His fighting instincts
are sharp.

400
00:18:17,583 --> 00:18:19,875
But he's not ready
to beat Tenma Hikage.

401
00:18:21,041 --> 00:18:22,500
Then again,

402
00:18:22,583 --> 00:18:24,291
perhaps that's why
he challenged him.

403
00:18:25,666 --> 00:18:27,541
Even in sumo,
there are wrestlers

404
00:18:27,625 --> 00:18:30,625
who evolve rapidly
following an upset victory.

405
00:18:32,250 --> 00:18:33,833
He's trying to break
out of his shell.

406
00:18:34,833 --> 00:18:36,666
Fighting isn't enough for him.

407
00:18:36,750 --> 00:18:39,583
Only an upset will free him!

408
00:18:39,666 --> 00:18:41,083
Strongest!

409
00:18:41,166 --> 00:18:42,041
[straining]

410
00:18:42,125 --> 00:18:43,500
-Yes!
-Yes!

411
00:18:44,791 --> 00:18:46,666
Tenma grabbed first!

412
00:18:46,750 --> 00:18:48,416
♪

413
00:18:48,500 --> 00:18:51,166
His right hand's inside
and his left is high!

414
00:18:51,250 --> 00:18:52,166
The perfect grip!

415
00:18:52,250 --> 00:18:53,583
Yeah, boy!

416
00:18:53,666 --> 00:18:55,416
Get him, Tenma!

417
00:18:55,500 --> 00:18:57,833
♪

418
00:18:58,833 --> 00:18:59,875
[SADA]
I thought you were working

419
00:18:59,958 --> 00:19:01,416
on a cross-grip sumo style.

420
00:19:02,500 --> 00:19:05,875
So how come you're ignoring
the mawashi belt so much?

421
00:19:05,958 --> 00:19:07,833
Heh. The thing that
scares me about you

422
00:19:07,916 --> 00:19:10,166
is that I have no idea
what's going through your head.

423
00:19:11,458 --> 00:19:12,958
[CHIHIRO]
All that technical junk,

424
00:19:13,041 --> 00:19:15,833
thrust-and-punch,
cross-grip, blah, blah.

425
00:19:15,916 --> 00:19:17,375
I can't beat specialists
like you

426
00:19:17,458 --> 00:19:20,458
if I get caught up
worrying about specifics.

427
00:19:20,541 --> 00:19:21,958
Huh?

428
00:19:22,041 --> 00:19:23,875
You said you're scared
'cause you have no idea

429
00:19:23,958 --> 00:19:25,750
what I'm thinking about, right?

430
00:19:25,833 --> 00:19:27,250
Suits me just fine.

431
00:19:27,333 --> 00:19:29,041
That's my style of choice.

432
00:19:30,125 --> 00:19:32,416
I want to be unsettling!

433
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:34,500
[TENMA]
Huh? What's he doing?

434
00:19:34,583 --> 00:19:36,000
And what's this dark aura?

435
00:19:36,083 --> 00:19:38,041
♪

436
00:19:38,125 --> 00:19:40,375
[CHIHIRO]
I want to be stronger!

437
00:19:40,458 --> 00:19:41,916
Stronger!

438
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,583
And the only way...

439
00:19:43,666 --> 00:19:45,291
that's gonna happen...

440
00:19:45,375 --> 00:19:47,875
is by causing an upset!

441
00:19:47,958 --> 00:19:49,958
-That move!
-Did he just...

442
00:19:50,041 --> 00:19:53,000
[CHIHIRO]
Neo Chihiro Special Number One!

443
00:19:54,125 --> 00:19:57,625
Shoot Down!

444
00:19:57,708 --> 00:19:58,708
[gasps]

445
00:19:58,791 --> 00:19:59,708
[ALL gasp]

446
00:19:59,791 --> 00:20:00,625
[chuckles]

447
00:20:00,708 --> 00:20:01,625
[BOTH gasp]

448
00:20:01,708 --> 00:20:03,166
[ALL cheering]

449
00:20:03,250 --> 00:20:05,166
[MAN 5]
He beat last year's bronze!

450
00:20:05,250 --> 00:20:07,166
[MAN 6]
Dachi High's unstoppable!

451
00:20:07,250 --> 00:20:08,125
[CROWD cheering]

452
00:20:09,250 --> 00:20:11,416
[HINOMARU] People who let common
sense control their actions

453
00:20:11,500 --> 00:20:13,875
place a wall between themselves
and national treasures.

454
00:20:13,958 --> 00:20:16,041
They build them up as special.

455
00:20:16,125 --> 00:20:18,875
An opponent they have absolutely
no chance of defeating.

456
00:20:18,958 --> 00:20:21,916
But Chihiro
doesn't believe in walls.

457
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:23,041
Only distance.

458
00:20:24,208 --> 00:20:26,750
That's why he can charge ahead
without any fear.

459
00:20:27,958 --> 00:20:29,750
And the thing
about guys like him,

460
00:20:29,833 --> 00:20:32,750
is that they're usually
the ones who cause an upset.

461
00:20:32,833 --> 00:20:35,250
[ANNOUNCER] Uh, Kunisaki
on the east side wins

462
00:20:35,333 --> 00:20:37,791
with, um,
a kimono-string drop.

463
00:20:37,875 --> 00:20:40,500
A kimono what?
The hell is that?

464
00:20:40,583 --> 00:20:42,416
Wait, so you executed
a technique

465
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:43,750
the pros rarely use

466
00:20:43,833 --> 00:20:45,333
without even knowing
what it's called?

467
00:20:45,416 --> 00:20:46,583
Unbelievable!

468
00:20:46,666 --> 00:20:48,458
He was operating
on pure instinct!

469
00:20:48,541 --> 00:20:50,625
You're a scary dude,
you know that?

470
00:20:50,708 --> 00:20:52,666
Sure it may be a sumo technique,

471
00:20:52,750 --> 00:20:55,750
but it goes completely
against traditional norms.

472
00:20:55,833 --> 00:20:58,625
So in other words,
it fits Kunisaki to a T.

473
00:20:58,708 --> 00:21:01,458
♪

474
00:21:01,541 --> 00:21:02,916
My national treasure name?

475
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:04,208
Yeah, man.

476
00:21:04,291 --> 00:21:06,041
If you beat one,
you gotta have a moniker.

477
00:21:06,125 --> 00:21:07,750
That's how it goes.

478
00:21:07,833 --> 00:21:09,041
Screw that.

479
00:21:09,125 --> 00:21:10,541
Those are only for guys
who are interested

480
00:21:10,625 --> 00:21:12,208
in becoming a yokozuna.

481
00:21:12,291 --> 00:21:14,666
I want to be the best mixed
martial artist in the world,

482
00:21:14,750 --> 00:21:16,541
and nothing's changing that.

483
00:21:18,708 --> 00:21:21,208
Still, if I had to choose.

484
00:21:21,291 --> 00:21:23,916
And it's not like I've been
thinking about it or anything.

485
00:21:26,125 --> 00:21:29,166
My official title
is Chihiro Kunisaki.

486
00:21:29,250 --> 00:21:31,916
The "National Treasure Eater!"

487
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:37,875
♪

488
00:21:37,958 --> 00:21:41,333
♪

489
00:21:41,416 --> 00:21:42,833
[BOTH chuckle]

490
00:21:42,916 --> 00:21:44,416
[ALL chuckle]

491
00:21:44,500 --> 00:21:45,708
[OZEKI]
Ushio!

492
00:21:45,791 --> 00:21:48,083
♪

493
00:21:50,791 --> 00:21:51,833
[laughs]

494
00:21:51,916 --> 00:21:55,958
♪

495
00:23:26,458 --> 00:23:29,291
National Treasures?
Yeah, I eat 'em!

496
00:23:29,375 --> 00:23:31,500
Explains my name.
I'm "The Kid."

497
00:23:31,583 --> 00:23:32,791
[ALL]
Huh?

498
00:23:32,875 --> 00:23:34,916
You know, 'cause kids
are always hungry.

499
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:36,666
-Uh, sure.
-Yeah, no.

500
00:23:36,750 --> 00:23:37,916
Uh...

